@wordwrap
@help HELP

@node MAIN "Ermmm... Is anyone reading this?"

Do You like OS3.5 icons? You do not own OS3.5 package? Is it hopeless?
The answer is simple: NO ;)

This small utility does convert OS3.5 PaletteMapped icons into NewIcons.
Whole hard job is made by Convert35Icon. All You have to do is specify some
arguments. Not too hard isn't it? ;)

 @{" Installation " link INSTALL}
 @{" Requirements " link REQ}
 @{" Features " link FEATURES}
 @{" Usage " link USAGE}
 @{" BUGS " link BUGS}
 @{" History " link HISTORY}
 @{" Credits " link CREDITS}
 @{" Author " link AUTHOR}

@endnode
@node INSTALL "How to install?"
Installation:
Just copy the specified executable ('Convert35Icon'/'@{"Convert35Icon_OS31" link OS31}') wherever You want...

Or use supplied installer script...

@endnode
@node REQ "Is 603e/333 needed?"

Requirements:
-OS3.5 to make it fully functional
-OS3.1 to run '@{"special" link OS31}' version of Convert35Icon... Read about it @{"here" link OS31}
-newicon.library V40+
-asl.library V38+

@endnode
@node FEATURES "Does it play Chess?"

Features:
-long names support (up to 103 characters)
-small size
-simply usage(CLI,WB)
-may strip PaletteMapped icon
-may strip Planar icon (ONLY OS3.5 version!)

@endnode
@node USAGE "Say HELLO"

Usage:

From CLI:
Source/A:
  source icon (PaletteMapped)
Dest/A:
  destination icon (NewIcon)
KEEPPALETTEMAPPED=KPM/S:
  Convert35Icon won't try to remove PaletteMapped icon image from destination
KEEPSTANDARD=KP/S:
  Convert35Icon won't try to remove Plain icon image from destination

Note:
1. You may specify source/dest with or without '@{b}.info@{ub}' extension.
2. KEEPSTANDARD works @{b}only@{ub} in OS3.5 version (not the @{"patched one)" link OS31}

From Workbench:
Just doubleclick Convert35Icon and a aslfilerequester will popup.
Or drop some icons on it.

If You do not want to be asked everytime set some tooltypes:
'STRIPPALETTEMAPPED' - always try to strip OS3.5 icon image
'KEEPPALETTEMAPPED' - do not try to remove it
'STRIPPLAIN' - always try to strip plain icon data
'KEEPPLAIN' - do not try to remove it

@{b}WARNING: When using from WB selected icon will be overwritten!!!@{ub}

@endnode
@node BUGS "I need a blueberry"

BUGS:
None found (Yet;)

@endnode
@node OS31 "ColorMapped on OS3.1? Naaa ;)"

Convert35Icon and OS3.1 Notes:
So You want to convert OS3.5 icons to NewIcons and You do NOT have OS3.5 installed?
Yes? So read on...

You may do it by @{"hand" link HAND}:
Or using installation script...

The choice is Yours ;)


NOTE: It MAY work on OS3.0 (NOT tested though)

@endnode
@node HAND "Let's rock"

 First You @{b}need @{ub}to get @{i}icon.library@{ui} V44+
  (OS3.5 relase, OS3.5 BoingBag1 relase, OS3.5 DOpus relase supported)

Second apply the patch to Convert35Icon by typing this into console:
 'gpatch Convert35Icon patches.ptg Convert35Icon_OS31'

Then copy the new executable as Convert35Icon anywhere You want...

Now the last stage
 'gpatch icon.library patches.ptg LIBS:ic35.library'
 (This is icon.library V44+, remember?)

Done!
Now You may convert any OS3.5 icon to NewIcon without installed OS3.5...


@endnode



